Granted, we had a reservation for a large party toward closing time, but verified that it wouldn't be an issue prior to making the reservation. We were seated fairly quickly and were given menus. Because we knew the timing we had, we ordered everything at one time to save time. It took 45 minutes to get our first round of drinks, over an hour to get any kind of food, and the servers were upset that we kept asking about the timing. We had a party of 8 people, a few of whom also placed to go orders. The to go orders came out first, and 1 entrée came out 35 minutes before everyone else's. We had to ask for water and napkins because neither was provided. The food was ok at best, and brought out cold. Definitely not my first choice for Mexican food.

They looked at me like I was crazy and I didn't know what I ordered. they still charged for the margarita even though I ordered a cheaper beverage. Added 25% gratuity automatically for a table of 4. I understand these are tough times, but 25% is a bit much and should be listed on the menu. I went there for my birthday with my significant other and we did not have a great experience. I decided to go there because they had a burrito if flavored margaritas and I wanted to try as many as I could! We started ordering a passion fruit one and a half pitcher of sangria. Our drinks were so strong we couldn't even finish them. When the waitress took our drinks order we said we needed a little time to order food. By the time she brought the drinks we were ready to order but she dropped off the drinks and walked away. It took a while hour of me trying to get her attention until a different waitress noticed me and came to get our order. Another couple sat next to our table after we had been seated and they had already gotten their drinks and we're finishing the food and we still hadn't ordered. By the time our food arrived we were so hungry and so drunk off those cocktails that we honestly don't know if the food was that good. We ate it all and I think it was nice but my partner thought their steak was very dry. We were really so hungry we even ordered chips and salsa after the meal because the portions also weren't big enough. The second waitress was the one who came to check on us and see if we needed anything else and brought us the check. She was clearly not the waitress designated to our section but we never saw our waitress again. She waited everyone else around us and completely forgot about us. I was so excited to go there for my birthday and I'm sad to say I'll never be going back.

Ordered the margarita and tried to order a water at the same time.  Was told I had to ask someone else for water...wha? When the margarita got here - Literally pure lime juice with absolutely zero tequila. YUCK. I really wanted a water.  I waited and waited and finally was able to waive someone down to ask for water. Sure, they say...and then no water...for 10 more minutes.  I eventually had to walk up to the bar and order one. Ordered enchilladas.  Asked for chicken and cheese.  Assured it came with cheese.  No cheese...just dry as chicken and rice and beans the consistency of baby vomit. No one came to ask how our food was.  No water, no one for drink refills or orders.
